    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"609515\">Kevin Carlson</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/411257-theory.3A-mathematics/topic/tangent.20space.20of.20power.20object.20in.20smooth.20sets/near/437502338\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm a bit confused about your end expression, but $\\Omega^{\\mathbb R^n}(X)=\\mathbf{Sh}(\\mathbf{Cart})(X\\times \\mathbb R^n,\\Omega)=\\Omega(X\\times \\mathbb R^n)$ should be the set of closed sieves on $X\\times \\mathbb R^n,$ no?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>🤦🏻‍♂️ I switched base and exponent in the formula... Then of course it reduces to what you say.</p>",
